		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've recently picked up again interest in making NES game and I'm going through these tutorials: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.retrocollect.com/News/learn-how-to-make-your-own-nintendo-nes-games.html">http://www.retrocollect.com/News/learn- ... games.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />However I've noticed those are using outdated and not that user-friendly NESASM.<br /><br />Do anyone know tutorials similar in style, but using NESHLA?

		

